All are at least somewhat bell-shapedâ€¦ although there are a lot of fizes that seem likely to be unrelated to movement from place to place, rather they are â€˜milling aboutâ€™ in place - such as at basecamp, at experiment sites, at rest stops, etc.

We can try filtering by the spatial density of GPS fixes.

Filter data by density of fixes

hexes <- all_traces |>
  st_make_grid(cellsize = 60, square = FALSE, what = "polygons") |>
  st_as_sf(crs = st_crs(all_traces))
counts <- hexes |>
  st_intersects(all_traces) |>
  lengths()
hexes <- hexes |>
  mutate(n = counts) |>
  filter(n > 0)

Map it with tmap (greater flexibility on the classification scheme)

tm_shape(hexes) +
  tm_fill(col = "n", style = "quantile", n = 20, palette = "-magma") +
  tm_layout(legend.outside = TRUE)
all_traces |>
  st_filter(hexes |> filter(n < 6)) |>
  ggplot(aes(x = slope_h, y = speed_km_h)) +
  geom_point(size = 0.5, alpha = 0.25) +
  geom_smooth()
